The paper deals with the fundamental limits of reliable communication over Finite State Channels (FSCs) with feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of feedback in controlling the availability or quality of feedback, which is related to control systems (cs.SY). The paper mentions the use of code trees, which is a common technique in coding theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the capacity of coding on the backward link, which is related to multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of causally conditioned distributions, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
